description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:1556-1564

  if (nonce == MESHTASTIC_CONFIG_STAGE_STATIC) {
      ret = enqueue_static_sync(adapter, &info);
  } else if (nonce == MESHTASTIC_CONFIG_STAGE_NODEDB) {
      ret = enqueue_node_sync(adapter, &info, &peers);
  } else {
      ret = enqueue_static_sync(adapter, &info);
      if (ret == 0) {
          ret = enqueue_node_sync(adapter, &info, &peers);
      }
  }
  if (ret < 0) {
      return ret;
  }
  return config_complete(adapter, nonce);

The return value of config_complete() is returned directly. If config_complete fails (e.g., enqueue_from_radio fails), the error is correctly propagated.

However, at this point partial sync data has already been enqueued. The client receives sync records but no config_complete, leaving it in an inconsistent state.

Consider adding documentation about this failure mode or implementing recovery (though recovery may not be practical in embedded context).
